gate.util.persistence

Class PersistenceManager.SlashDevSlashNull

  • java.lang.Object
    • gate.util.persistence.PersistenceManager.SlashDevSlashNull
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Persistence, Serializable
    Enclosing class:
    PersistenceManager

    public static class PersistenceManager.SlashDevSlashNull
extends Object
implements Persistence
    This class is used as a marker for types that should NOT be serialised when saving the state of a gate object. Registering this type as the persistent equivalent for a specific class (via PersistenceManager.registerPersistentEquivalent(Class , Class)) effectively stops all values of the specified type from being serialised. Maps that contain values that should not be serialised will have that entry removed. In any other places where such values occur they will be replaced by null after deserialisation.
